low++;
high++;

👉 This is the key idea:

The window moves forward continuously
Not in rigid jumps
🔥 This changes everything

Instead of:

[0–20] → DONE → [20–40] → DONE

You get:

[0–20]
[1–21]
[2–22]
[3–23]
...

👉 That’s the sliding window

8️⃣ Why sliding window is better
Without it:
You rotate a lot to find rare remaining values
With it:
You accept nearby values
Reduce rotations drastically
